f:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX calculates funding rates hourly using a mark price derived from multiple spot exchanges and the perpetual's premium to spot. The funding exchange occurs at the top of each hour, with longs paying shorts when rates are positive. Starknet's validity proofs ensure settlement integrity while off-chain matching provides sub-second execution. Cross-margin positions automatically use available collateral to maintain funding payments without manual intervention."}]
10:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ARB","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ARB/USDT on RabbitX benefits from Arbitrum's native token dynamics and the exchange's L2-focused user base. The pair often exhibits funding rate premiums during Arbitrum ecosystem developments or governance events. RabbitX's hourly settlement frequency provides more arbitrage opportunities compared to 8-hour cycles on other exchanges."}]]}]
11:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ARB/USDT funding rates on RabbitX have shown strong correlation with Arbitrum network activity and governance proposals. During major ecosystem announcements, rates frequently spike above 0.1% hourly as traders take leveraged positions. The hourly settlement creates more volatile rate swings compared to traditional 8-hour cycles. Weekend rates tend to normalize due to reduced institutional activity, while weekday volatility aligns with traditional market hours."}]]}]
12:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX's hourly funding provides 24 opportunities daily compared to 3 on most exchanges, creating frequent arbitrage windows. The DEX's limited liquidity can cause funding rates to diverge significantly from CEX counterparts during high volatility. Cross-margin functionality allows efficient capital utilization across multiple positions for delta-neutral strategies. Zero gas fees eliminate the cost friction that typically erodes small arbitrage profits on other L2 derivatives platforms."}]]}]
13:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX's early-stage status presents protocol risk despite Starknet's security guarantees. Limited liquidity can cause significant slippage during position adjustments, especially for larger arbitrage sizes. The exchange's small user base may result in extended periods of extreme funding rates without natural market correction. Insurance fund coverage remains unproven compared to established exchanges, requiring careful position sizing and risk assessment."}]]}]
14:["$","$L16",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are ARB/USDT funding rates calculated on RabbitX?","answer":"RabbitX calculates and settles funding rates hourly for ARB/USDT perpetuals. This provides 24 settlement opportunities per day, compared to the standard 8-hour cycles used by most centralized exchanges."},{"question":"Does RabbitX charge gas fees for ARB/USDT funding payments?","answer":"No, RabbitX operates on Starknet with zero gas fees for all trading activities including funding payments. This makes frequent funding rate arbitrage strategies more profitable compared to other L2 derivatives platforms."},{"question":"What are the maker and taker fees for ARB/USDT on RabbitX?","answer":"RabbitX charges 0.02% maker fees and 0.05% taker fees for ARB/USDT perpetual futures. These competitive rates help preserve arbitrage profits, especially when combined with zero gas costs for position management."},{"question":"Can I use cross-margin for ARB/USDT funding rate strategies?","answer":"Yes, RabbitX supports cross-margin trading which automatically uses available collateral across all positions. This feature is particularly useful for delta-neutral funding rate strategies where you maintain offsetting positions across different pairs."}]}]
